# 42-ui: Responsive Admin Tables (>=1280px vs <1280px)

Applies to dense CRUD tables in admin UI.

## Desktop (>=1280px)
- Use a multi-column table.
- Keep drag handle column narrow (`w-10`) and consistent.
- Avoid fixed widths that cause horizontal scroll unless truly necessary.

## Mobile (<1280px): two-column pattern
- Table becomes 2 columns:
  1) **Handle** (narrow, e.g. `w-5`)
  2) **Content** (flex-1) that stacks info vertically

### Content column structure (required)
1) **Header**: `"{index}. {name}"` (index is part of the title, NOT a separate column)
   - Status badge goes under the title by default (`flex-col`) so it wraps naturally.
2) **Details**: key/value rows
   - description wraps (`whitespace-normal break-words`) and is capped around `max-w-[35ch]`
   - meta fields use `text-sm text-muted-foreground`
3) **Actions**: icon-only buttons on mobile
   - `flex items-center gap-2`

## FORBIDDEN
- ❌ Separate "№" column on mobile.
- ❌ Text labels on action buttons on mobile (icons only).
- ❌ `whitespace-nowrap` on description/details that must wrap.
